 "cells": [
  {

   "id": "dominant-meeting",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Compute climate metrics"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "unusual-illustration",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import sys\n",
    "\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from scipy.stats import lognorm\n",
    "\n",
    "# to give us access to the root when climate metrics is not installed locally\n",
    "sys.path.append('..')\n",
    "from climate_metrics import (\n",
    "    GWP,\n",
    "    GTP,\n",
    "    cumulative_radiative_forcing,\n",
    "    temperature_response\n",
    ")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "advance-heating",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### An emission of 1 kg CO$_2$ or CH$_4$."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "vocational-saudi",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "GWP 100 for emitting 1 kg co2: 1 (kg CO2 eq)\n",
      "GTP 100 for emitting 1 kg co2: 1 (kg CO2 eq)\n",
      "GWP 100 for emitting 1 kg ch4: 28 (kg CO2 eq)\n",
      "GTP 100 for emitting 1 kg ch4: 4 (kg CO2 eq) \n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "time_period = 100\n",
    "time_horizon = np.arange(time_period+1)\n",
    "emission = 1  # 1 kg of CO2\n",
    "GHG='co2'\n",
    "\n",
    "gwp = GWP(time_period, emission, GHG)\n",
    "gtp = GTP(time_period, emission, GHG)\n",
    "print(f'GWP {time_period} for emitting 1 kg {GHG}: {gwp:.0f} (kg CO2 eq)')\n",
    "print(f'GTP {time_period} for emitting 1 kg {GHG}: {gtp:.0f} (kg CO2 eq)')\n",
    "\n",
    "GHG='ch4'\n",
    "gwp = GWP(time_period, emission, GHG)\n",
    "gtp = GTP(time_period, emission, GHG)\n",
    "print(f'GWP {time_period} for emitting 1 kg {GHG}: {gwp:.0f} (kg CO2 eq)')\n",
    "print(f'GTP {time_period} for emitting 1 kg {GHG}: {gtp:.0f} (kg CO2 eq) ')"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "earned-efficiency",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### For an emission scenario"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "dangerous-december",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "GWP 100 of baseline scenario: 56 kg CO2 eq\n",
      "GTP 100 of baseline scenario: 108 kg CO2 eq\n",
      "GWP 100 of project scenario: 34 kg CO2 eq\n",
      "GTP 100 of project scenario: 52 kg CO2 eq\n"
     ]
    },
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "# parameters\n",
    "baseline_emission_scenario = np.ones(time_period+1)\n",
    "project_emission_scenario = lognorm.sf(time_horizon, s=np.log(2.5), loc=0, scale=40)\n",
    "GHG = 'CO2'\n",
    "\n",
    "# gwp calculations\n",
    "gwp_baseline = GWP(time_period, baseline_emission_scenario, GHG, annual=False)\n",
    "print(f'GWP {time_period} of baseline scenario: {gwp_baseline:.0f} kg CO2 eq')\n",
    "gtp_baseline = GTP(time_period, baseline_emission_scenario, GHG, annual=False)\n",
    "print(f'GTP {time_period} of baseline scenario: {gtp_baseline:.0f} kg CO2 eq')\n",
    "gwp_project = GWP(time_period, project_emission_scenario, GHG, annual=False)\n",
    "print(f'GWP {time_period} of project scenario: {gwp_project:.0f} kg CO2 eq')\n",
    "gtp_project = GTP(time_period, project_emission_scenario, GHG, annual=False)\n",
    "print(f'GTP {time_period} of project scenario: {gtp_project:.0f} kg CO2 eq')\n",
    "\n",
    "# plot\n",
    "plt.plot(baseline_emission_scenario, label='baseline')\n",
    "plt.plot(project_emission_scenario, label='project')\n",
    "plt.title(\"emission scenarios\", size=16)\n",
    "plt.ylim((0,1.05))\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Annual emissions CO2 (kg)')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('years')\n",
    "_ = plt.legend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "emotional-viewer",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Going under the hood of GWP and GTP\n",
    "\n",
    "We can look at the underlying physical reponse of the models used to generate GWP and GTP. GWP is a relative measure of cumlative radiative forcing (measured in Watts * meter<sup>-2</sup> * yr) which captures the sum of the energy imbalance at the tropopause caused by a GHG emission. GTP is a relative measure of the global average temperature response (measured in Kelvin) caused by a GHG emission."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "confidential-motor",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "crf_baseline = cumulative_radiative_forcing(\n",
    "    time_period,\n",
    "    baseline_emission_scenario,\n",
    "    'CO2',\n",
    "    step_size=1,\n",
    "    annual=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "crf_project = cumulative_radiative_forcing(\n",
    "    time_period,\n",
    "    project_emission_scenario,\n",
    "    'CO2',\n",
    "    step_size=1,\n",
    "    annual=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(crf_baseline, label='baseline')\n",
    "plt.plot(crf_project, label='project')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('cumulative radiative forcing ($W m^{-2} yr$)')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('year')\n",
    "plt.title('Cumulative radiative forcing')\n",
    "_ = plt.legend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "addressed-summary",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "temp_baseline = temperature_response(\n",
    "    time_period,\n",
    "    baseline_emission_scenario,\n",
    "    'CO2',\n",
    "    step_size=1,\n",
    "    annual=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "temp_project = temperature_response(\n",
    "    time_period,\n",
    "    project_emission_scenario,\n",
    "    'CO2',\n",
    "    step_size=1,\n",
    "    annual=True)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.plot(temp_baseline, label='baseline')\n",
    "plt.plot(temp_project, label='project')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('temperature response ($K$)')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('year')\n",
    "plt.title('Temperature response')\n",
    "_ = plt.legend()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "innocent-wisdom",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### GWP and GTP at different time points\n",
    "\n",
    "While it is common to use GWP 100, we can look at these metrics at different time horizons."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "sufficient-cosmetic",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "gwp_baseline = GWP(time_period, baseline_emission_scenario, GHG, annual=True)\n",
    "gwp_project = GWP(time_period, project_emission_scenario, GHG, annual=True)\n",
    "plt.plot(gwp_baseline, label='baseline')\n",
    "plt.plot(gwp_project, label='project')\n",
    "plt.title(\"\")\n",
    "plt.ylabel('GWP (kg CO2eq)')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('time horizon (years)')\n",
    "_ = plt.legend()"
   ]
  },

    "plt.plot(gtp_baseline, label='baseline')\n",
